Lvivsky Avtozavod, a Ukrainian maker
of buses, will seek to assemble buses and trollies in  Bulgaria 
and  Russia  to boost sales abroad,  Kommersant-Ukraine  reported,
citing Oleksandr Lobko, director of Citi Transport Group which
manages LAZ.  LAZ is considering buying plants or entering joint ventures
in Sofia and Gabrovo in Bulgaria as well as acquiring plants in
Russia with a capacity of 1,000 vehicles a year, according to
Kommersant. LAZ wants to sell buses assembled in Bulgaria to
customers in Romania and Serbia, Kommersant cited Lobko as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
